messages.text: I‚Äôm sorry I haven‚Äôt called or anything.
S‚Äôall right. You said you needed time.
I‚Äôm working and taking meetings. But that‚Äôs about it.
B, listen. I never wanted anyone to get hurt.
Mom and Dad blamed me, too.
I‚Äôm the one who sent our girl running.
The three of us have always been tight.
I hate us fighting and being apart like we are.
I hate it, too. But there‚Äôs something I need to understand.
Why didn‚Äôt you tell me how you felt about Taylor?
You‚Äôre my brother. You always came first. With everyone.
Don‚Äôt pull that crap about me being the favorite.
It‚Äôs not crap ‚Äî I was the loser with no future.
Destined to live in Mom and Dad‚Äôs basement.
And I was the one telling them they were wrong.
I needed someone to believe in me.
So, let me ask you again‚Ä¶why didn‚Äôt you tell me?
That‚Äôs why I couldn‚Äôt tell you.
I would have let you have her. All you had to do was tell me the truth.
You‚Äôre right. I would‚Äôve flipped out and taken a swing at you.
And Mom would have sprayed us with the hose to separate us.
The hose was always her weapon of choice.
LMAO No. Guilt‚Äôs her favorite weapon.
Has she tried to make you feel guilty?
They didn‚Äôt have to try hard. I know what I did.
Just like I know I can‚Äôt take it back.
Would you take it back if you could?
You would have let us get married?
No, I just would have thought of a different way.
Maybe by taking you out and telling you how I felt.
As much as I think you should have been honest, me and Taylor were going through with it.
Yes, I do. You know it, too.
It‚Äôs why you did what you did.
Are you saying you‚Äôre glad I screwed up your ceremony?
Hell, no. It was the worst day of my life.
It was my worst day, too.
Tay and I were never going to make it.
We were trying for the baby.
After we lost him, we tried for us.
Yeah. But it didn‚Äôt work out.
Just like you and me should try to be.
I just don‚Äôt know where to start.
This is a start. A good one.

The day she blocked my calls.
